"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-27-lady-gaga-dancer-falls-stage-chaotic-olympics-ceremony-moment-21308686\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"All eyes were on last night's Paris 2024Olympicsopening ceremony asCeline Dion wowed the crowdandLady Gagaperformed on the Seine River - except not everything went to plan for the latter.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 187, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 30, \"end\": 35, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2879104627981205e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Bad Romance hitmaker, 38, performed a spirited rendition of Mon Truc En Plumes' on a set of stairs wearing a big feathered pom pom on the back of a black leotard.\", \"from\": 189, \"to\": 355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She and the 10 dancers, decked out in custom Dior costumes, kicked, spun and leapt to the fast-paced French classic, in what was an electrifying performance to open the ceremony.\", \"from\": 357, \"to\": 535, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 458, \"end\": 472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French classic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, after a rainy day in Paris, one of the dancers slipped and fell on stage mid-kick, as his pink pom poms could be seen dropping out of sight.\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 567, \"end\": 572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2879104627981205e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Luckily, his recovery was pretty impressive, as the dancer leapt back up - looking a little bit perplexed at his fall - and carried on with the show as Gaga spun above the heads of his colleagues.\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.732077497465259e-41, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The House of Gucci star did not mention this incident in a post-performance message shared on social media, saying how 'completely grateful' she felt to have been asked to perform.\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 1066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just a small slip up\\u2026 \\u00f0\\u009f\\u0098\\u00b2The show must go on, whatever the weather!\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0098\\u0094\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f#Olympics#Paris2024pic.twitter.com/Xj3H5z5vI0  Taking to X, she wrote: 'I feel so completely grateful to have been asked to open the Paris @Olympics 2024 this year.\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1276, \"end\": 1281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2879104627981205e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I am also humbled to be asked by the Olympics organising committee to sing such a special French song - a song to honour the French people and their tremendous history of art, music, and theatre.'\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1400, \"end\": 1406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9985334037770884, \"rank\": 0.0008853793559086223, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1435, \"end\": 1448, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Born This Way hitmaker explained how Zizi Jeanmarie, who was born in Paris a French ballerina, famously sang the track - which translates to My Thing with Feathers - in 1961.\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1549, \"end\": 1553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 7.028528857518901e-12, \"text\": \"Zizi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\"}, {\"begin\": 1581, \"end\": 1586, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2879104627981205e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The pair crossed paths when Zizi starred in Cole Porter's Anything Goes musical, which was Gaga's first jazz release.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\", \"score\": 0.9999999999895408, \"rank\": 7.028528857518901e-12, \"text\": \"Zizi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zizi_Strallen\"}, {\"begin\": 1779, \"end\": 1783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.732077497465259e-41, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She continued: 'Although I am not a French artist, I have always felt a very special connection with French people and singing French music - I wanted nothing more than to create a performance that would warm the heart of France, celebrate French art and music, and on such a momentous occasion remind everyone of one of the most magical cities on earth - Paris.'\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 2170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1843, \"end\": 1849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9985334037770884, \"rank\": 0.0008853793559086223, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1908, \"end\": 1921, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French people\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_people\"}, {\"begin\": 1934, \"end\": 1940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9985334037770884, \"rank\": 0.0008853793559086223, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2029, \"end\": 2035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999816227503, \"rank\": 1.5269312833481978e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2047, \"end\": 2053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9985334037770884, \"rank\": 0.0008853793559086223, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2163, \"end\": 2168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2879104627981205e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the performance, Gaga and the dancers rented pom poms from French cabaret theatre Le Lido archive, which were made of 'naturally moulted' feathers.\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2193, \"end\": 2197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.732077497465259e-41, \"text\": \"Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 2235, \"end\": 2241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9985334037770884, \"rank\": 0.0008853793559086223, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2258, \"end\": 2265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Lido\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Lido\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Lido\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Lido\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I studied French choreography that put a modern twist on a French classic,' she explained.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2336, \"end\": 2342, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9985334037770884, \"rank\": 0.0008853793559086223, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2385, \"end\": 2399, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French classic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Classic_Races\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I rehearsed tirelessly to study a joyful French dance, brushing up on some old skills - I bet you did not know I used to dance at a 60's French party on the lower east side when I was first starting out!\", \"from\": 2418, \"to\": 2622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2460, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9985334037770884, \"rank\": 0.0008853793559086223, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2556, \"end\": 2568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Party\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Party\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I hope you love this performance as much as I do.\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2674, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And to everyone in France, thank you so much for welcoming me to your country to sing in honour of you - it's a gift I will never forget!\", \"from\": 2675, \"to\": 2812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2694, \"end\": 2700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999816227503, \"rank\": 1.5269312833481978e-08, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Congratulations to all the athletes who are competing in this year's Olympic Games!\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 2898, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is my supreme honour to sing for you and cheer you on!!\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2957, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Watching the Olympic Games always makes me cry!\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 3005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your talent is unimaginable.\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let the games begin!'\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere Celine Dion, 56, took to the stage later in the evening with an emotional performance - her first since sheannounced her diagnosis with the neurological condition stiff-person syndrome(SPS) almost two years ago.\", \"from\": 3058, \"to\": 3279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dion had cancelled her Las Vegas residency due to health concerns in 2021, before revealing her SPS diagnosis in December 2022 and cancelling her Courage World Tour.\", \"from\": 3281, \"to\": 3446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3304, \"end\": 3313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\", \"score\": 0.6659411373872435, \"rank\": 0.5016342189933652, \"text\": \"Las Vegas\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Las_Vegas_Strip\"}, {\"begin\": 3377, \"end\": 3380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\", \"score\": 0.4822950518465206, \"rank\": 0.722074542879511, \"text\": \"SPS\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Socialist_Party_of_Serbia\"}, {\"begin\": 3427, \"end\": 3445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courage_World_Tour\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Courage World Tour\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courage_World_Tour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Courage_World_Tour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": 